<h3 class="sectionedit9" id="are_ad_links_and_linking_to_modified_proprietary_firmware_blobs_allowed">Are ad links and linking to modified proprietary firmware blobs allowed?</h3>
<div class="level3">
<blockquote><div class="no">
 I ask this because of the official firmware links on <a href="../toh/tp-link/tl-wr841nd" class="wikilink1" title="toh:tp-link:tl-wr841nd">tl-wr841nd</a>&#039;s page. Three of the links are ad links that the uploader makes money off of which usually aren&#039;t allowed on forums or wiki pages. The fact that the links are to proprietary firmware blobs makes this much worse and likely illegal. Then there&#039;s the fact the the blobs are modified and re-hosted elsewhere which is also likely illegal. I suggest removing the links and just pointing to the relevant information on how to strip the firmware rather than potentially get the openwrt.org webmaster in trouble. — <em>bracket 2014/11/02 18:39</em></div></blockquote>

</div>
